Press Releases.Title: 2 New Cases of Locally Transmitted Covid-19 Infection (30 Oct)
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 30 October 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed 2 new cases of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection. Based on our investigations so far, 1 is in the community, and 1 resides in a dormitory.  

2      In addition, there are 7 imported cases, who had all been placed on Stay-Home Notice or isolated upon arrival in Singapore. In total, there are 9 new cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore today. 

3      We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.
